  "text": "Amazon Fire TV Stick $20 $35 Save $15 Setting the bar for affordable TV sticks for some time, Amazon's latest integrates Alexa into the remote and can be powered directly from your TV or monitor's USB port. Get it now for just $20. If you've been looking to upgrade your monitor and turn it into a smart TV, we recommend grabbing the Fire TV Stick HD from Amazon, which comes in at just $20 right now thanks to a great discount. You'll gain access to all your favorite video and game streaming services, and navigation is dead simple thanks to the smooth menu system, making it possible to just kick back, relax, and watch your shows. Related I turned my non-smart TV into an Android TV with Raspberry Pi — here’s how you can too If you want to modernize your older TV, you can use a Raspberry Pi to turn it into an Android TV. What's great about the Amazon Fire TV HD? Source: Amazon You can't go wrong with Amazon's Fire TV devices, offering easy access to a variety of entertainment, like popular video streaming services, apps, and even game streaming services. The best part is that it's easy to get setup, requiring you to just plug it into any TV or monitor, and then you're on your way. You can also gain access to live TV services as well, and the remote even supports voice controls using Amazon's Alexa. You can even control compatible smart home products as well. Overall, not a bad purchase for just $20, especially if you're looking to take your monitor or TV to a new level. The great part is that once you're done with watching your shows, you just switch over your input to a new source, and you're back to your normal monitor experience. It doesn't get any easier or cheaper than this, which is why it's a great time to pick up an Amazon Fire TV Stick.",
